DIAGNOSIS. Small (
18.35 mm
) scorpions. Color is dark brown, lighter on the legs, with underlying mottling on carapace and mesosoma. (see 
Figure 1
). Pedipalp movable finger with 6 ID denticles and fixed finger with 5. Carapace of female is longer than the fifth metasomal segment. Pectinal tooth count for females 11.25 [n=12], males 13.20 [n=10]. Large, well developed subaculear tubercle.
